<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="rbwinst-pr" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Water Supply: Merging Objects</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para style="margin-bottom:10px; line-height:2.0;"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Water Supply: Merging Objects</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Some of the objects that were imported from the DXF file define zones of different thickness in the aquifer. However, those objects are discontinuous. They will need to be merged into single objects in order to be used. The key in the DXF file indicates what the different colors of objects represents. </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><table rowcount="4" colcount="2" style="width:auto; cell-padding:2px; cell-spacing:2px; page-break-inside:auto; border-width:1px; border-spacing:2px; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#000000; border-style:raised-color; background-color:none; head-row-background-color:none; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Header"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Color</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Header"><text styleclass="Table Header" translate="true">Thickness</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Cell" style="text-align:center;"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">green</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Cell" style="text-align:center;"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">10 ft</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Cell" style="text-align:center;"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">blue</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Cell" style="text-align:center;"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">20 ft</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Cell" style="text-align:center;"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">aqua</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Table Cell" style="text-align:center;"><text styleclass="Table Cell" translate="true">40 ft</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The colored grid makes it a little difficult to see the objects so it is helpful to hide the grid. First turn off the grid coloring by selecting </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Data|Color Grid...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> </text><image src="ColorGirdButton.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Normal"><title translate="true">Color Grid button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, select "none" and click the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Apply</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button. Then click on the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Show 2-D gridlines</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button </text><image src="ShowGridLines.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and select </text><image src="ShowGridOutline.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">Show exterior</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. The grid lines in the 2-D view will disappear except for those that show the selected column, row, and layer.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Next select the two blue objects near the south end of the model. (Click on the first one to select it then hold down the Shift key and click on the second one.) Then right click on the top view of the model and select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Merge objects...</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to merge the objects (fig. 124). Hide the object after the objects have been merged.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:center;"><table rowcount="3" colcount="2" style="width:auto; cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; page-break-inside:auto; border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; cell-border-width:0px; border-style:none; background-color:none; head-row-background-color:none; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupply2ObjectsSelected.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupply2ObjectsMerged.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true">A</text></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true">B</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 124</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true">. Objects (A) before and (B) after merging.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Repeat the process with the other blue objects and then with the green objects (figs. 125-126.).</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupply2ObjectsMerged2.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 125.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> Additional blue objects after being merged.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupply2ObjectsMerged10Ft.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 126.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> Green objects after being merged</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Finally, repeat the process with the aqua objects( figs. 127-128). There is one very short section of aqua objects that is easy to miss (fig. 127). Be sure to get it.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupplyShortObject.ipp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 127.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> Small aqua-colored object selected.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupplyAquiferThickness.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 128.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> Aqua-colored objects merged.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Finally, click the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Show or hide objects</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button </text><image src="ShowHideObjectsButton.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">Show or Hide Objects button</title></image><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. Click on </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">All Objects</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> twice to show all the objects. Then uncheck on Set Grid Cell Size to hide the domain outline. The final result is illustrated in figure 129.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="WaterSupplyMergedObjects.bmp" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption"><title translate="true">See caption</title></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Image Caption"><text styleclass="Image Number" translate="true">Figure 129.</text><text styleclass="Image Caption" translate="true"> All merged objects.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
